The paper discusses reinforcement learning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. Specifically, it focuses on Q-learning, which is a popular model-free algorithm. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the paper deals with theoretical analysis of a learning algorithm. Additionally, the paper discusses exploration-exploitation trade-offs, which are relevant to multi-agent systems, making cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses episodic MDPs, which are relevant to robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category as well.
